The parents of ISIS hostage Peter Kassig have issued another public plea to his captors - emphasizing that he is now a Muslim and wants to 'serve God and teach Islam.'

The tweet, sent out on his mother Paula Kassig's Twitter account, was written entirely in Arabic. 

In the message, they refer to Peter Kassig by his Muslim name: Abdul-Rahman.

'His father and I have done everything in our power to fulfill what you’ve asked of us. We are simple people who are faithful in helping others,' she writes. 

